header.name: NATE TANNER
header.title: APPLICATION DEVELOPER/SOFTWARE ENGINEER/FULL STACK DEVELOPER
header.summary: Highly motivated individual with experience in developing and implementing software solutions. Proven expertise in developing, testing, and debugging high performing software solutions with a keen eye for detail. Skilled in object-oriented programming, web development and database technologies. Excellent problem-solving and communication skills and demonstrates a passion for learning and implementing new technologies. Earned a certificate in Full Stack Web Development from the University of Utah (2023) and a bachelor’s degree in software engineering from the University of Phoenix (2011).
header.skills: Node.js, React.js, Express.js, JavaScript ES6+, CSS3, HTML5, SQL, NoSQL, GitHub, MongoDB, Handlebars, jQuery, PHP, Bootstrap, Databases (Oracle, MySQL). Experience in other programming languages, frameworks, and npm packages.

roles.title: Application Developer (Software Engineer)
duties: Develop applications used by the sales team for product demonstrations.
Using JavaScript, HTML, JSON, CSS to create applications.
Working with npm packages in Node.js
Debugging code to ensure proper run across browsers.
Working within a proprietary JavaScript based framework.
Creating and implementing source code for new applications.
Conducting unit and integration testing before launches.
Writing SQL statements for querying database and extracting data.
Implementing agile development practices across multiple projects, ensuring timely delivery of high-quality solutions within budget constraints.
Writing well-designed, testable code.

roles.title: Human Capital Management Demo Systems Analyst
duties: Project Manage key business partners, software developers and other technical resources to ensure timely updates that coincide with production version releases.
Work with product management, program development and IT and assess the impact and planning of the demonstration environments.
Development of demonstration processes and documentation of "how to" and training to the sales community.
Ensure peak sales effectiveness by collecting and incorporating sales field feedback into the demonstration environment.

roles.title: Application Developer (Software Engineer)
duties: Develop and deploy advanced scripts including integration with web services and databases.
Create programming solutions using Microsoft Visual Studio and inContact scripting software.
Develop and maintain costing for projects, perform risk analysis, and manage change control.
Create and manage project plans and project timelines.
Manage between 6 to 9 projects of various sizes concurrently.
Develop hour estimates for projects and monitor hours for compliance and budget.
Conduct comprehensive cost/benefit analysis and prepare business cases for projects.
Provide process, data, and object modeling in a variety of application and database environments (including MS Visio).
Managed projects and implementations for multi-billion dollar and Fortune 500 companies.

roles.title: Manager – Functional Experts
duties: Manage a team of 15 Functional Experts (Quality Assurance Analysts) with a solid reporting relationship.
All HR duties relating to a direct reporting relationship (hiring, discipline, coaching, etc.).
Manage global projects and initiatives including creating project plans, maintaining budget, managing timeline, process improvement, and ensuring scope.
Ensure that functional areas within operations are standardized.
